# TTS & User-Facing Text

## Sanitization
- Strip markdown before TTS: bold, code, headings, links (keep link text)
- Remove conventional commit prefixes (`feat:`, `fix:`, etc.)
- Remove ticket tags like `(MVP-017)`
- Use `_sanitize_for_speech()` in `tts/base.py` for LLM output

## LLM System Prompt
- Instruct Claude to respond in plain conversational language
- No markdown, no code blocks, no special formatting — output is spoken aloud

## Error Messages
- User-facing errors should be clear and actionable
- Avoid raw stack traces; log details, surface a friendly message
